getValueDataObject

public DataObject getValueDataObject()
Description copied from class: AbstractElement
When passing value through the query system, it could to be converted to a DataObject. This is especially useful for complex value objects. The system would check if this is set first, then check AbstractElement.getValueCodex(). It should be overridden by the subclass to set it if used.

Overrides:
getValueDataObject in class AbstractElement<java.util.Collection<AttributeNameValue<?>>,AttributeNameValue<?>,AttributeNameValue<?>>
Returns:
null by default, otherwise a DataObject representing the value if set.
See Also:
AbstractElement.getValueCodex()
